This paper involves deep learning for tomographic reconstructions, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a neural network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a prior for the desired image structures, which is a common topic in neural networks and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of gradient information, which is a common topic in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of limited view artefacts, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT).
